<HL>
   Spanish Agricultural Revenue
</HL>
<DATE>
12/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   MADRID -- Spanish agricultural revenue grew 4.5% to more
than 2 billion pesetas ($20.3 million) in 1990, said Spain's
agricultural minister, Carlos Romero.
   Olive production surged 38% to 551 metric tons in 1990
compared with the year before, earning the sector 148 billion
pesetas, the minister said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Wine production leaped 40% from 1989 figures to 42 million
hectoliters, valued at 168 million pesetas, he added.
