<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)
</IN>
<LP>
   LAGUNA NIGUEL, Calif. -- Furon Co. said it agreed to
dissolve its Japanese joint venture, NTN-Rulon, selling its
45% interest to partner NTN Corp. for about $16.5 million.
   The companies plan to continue mutual sales of products
and materials, and exchange information on new products and
technologies. The transaction is expected to close in late
January.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Furon, a maker of polymer products, said it will use the
proceeds to pay down long-term debt.
