   Fed Approves Joint Venture
</HL>
<DATE>
12/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C21
</SO>
<CO>
   Z.SBV
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
SECURITIES (SCR)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL RESERVE BOARD (FED)
</GV>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- The Federal Reserve Board approved an alliance
between Swiss Bank Corp. and the big Chicago options firm,
O'Connor Partners.
   The alliance between Triple-A rated Swiss Bank and
O'Connor marks another entry into the highly profitable
business of creating customized futures and options on
stocks, bonds, commodities, and currencies for investors.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Swiss Bank will tap O'Connor's trading talent and
technology, while O'Connor, a secretive proprietary trading
firm, will gain exposure to new clients through Swiss Bank's
franchise.
   The new unit will be called SBC/OC Services L.P., and will
be jointly owned by Swiss Bank and O'Connor Partners.
   The Federal Reserve Board announced the approval late last
week.
