   Bidermann said Collection Clothing is a joint venture of
Alexander Julian and Aeneas Venture Corp., an affiliate of
Harvard Management Group. Bidermann, major maker and
distributor of apparel under various brand and designer
names, is a unit of Bidermann S.A. of France. It acquired
Cluett for $350 million last March from distressed investor
William Farley, who needed to sell assets of West
Point-Pepperell Inc. after he acquired the textile company in
a leveraged buy-out.
